WEBVTT

1
00:00:12.167 --> 00:00:14.167
[theme music playing]

2
00:01:24.625 --> 00:01:25.917
[siren chirps]

3
00:01:26.000 --> 00:01:28.292
[reporter on TV] <i>As we await</i>
<i>more details out of Paris.</i>

4
00:01:28.375 --> 00:01:31.083
<i>we take a look back</i>
<i>on another life cut short.</i>

5
00:01:31.167 --> 00:01:33.125
<i>Professor Charles Xavier.</i>

6
00:01:33.208 --> 00:01:35.542
<i>The mutant leader's</i>
<i>assassination last year</i>

7
00:01:35.625 --> 00:01:38.375
<i>by former NSA agent Henry Gyrich</i>

8
00:01:38.458 --> 00:01:40.458
<i>has spurred increased sympathy</i>
<i>toward mutants</i>

9
00:01:40.542 --> 00:01:42.542
<i>despite their strange powers.</i>

10
00:01:42.625 --> 00:01:43.625
[grunts]

11
00:01:44.792 --> 00:01:46.958
<i>But is mankind ready to share a future</i>

12
00:01:47.042 --> 00:01:50.625
<i>with those who science claims</i>
<i>were born to replace us?</i>

13
00:01:50.708 --> 00:01:53.417
<i>Experts debate this</i>
<i>and more after the break.</i>

14
00:01:55.208 --> 00:01:59.708
[Mullet] The buyer's really gonna throw
down 10 grand for every mutant we nab?

15
00:02:00.375 --> 00:02:02.268
[Denti] Says he's using them
for target practice.

16
00:02:02.292 --> 00:02:03.292
[mimics gunshot]

17
00:02:04.333 --> 00:02:05.375
[grunts]

18
00:02:06.417 --> 00:02:07.417
Please don't hurt me.

19
00:02:07.500 --> 00:02:10.958
I'm Roberto da Costa.
heir to the Da Costa fortune.

20
00:02:11.042 --> 00:02:12.917
Name a price. Money's not an issue.

21
00:02:13.000 --> 00:02:14.833
[Denti] Mutie thinks it's about cash.

22
00:02:14.917 --> 00:02:15.917
Funny.

23
00:02:16.458 --> 00:02:18.083
What's this freak's trick?

24
00:02:18.167 --> 00:02:19.167
[Mullet] No clue.

25
00:02:19.250 --> 00:02:21.292
Kid didn't even try to use his powers.

26
00:02:21.375 --> 00:02:22.917
Collared him just in case.

27
00:02:23.500 --> 00:02:24.667
Hear that. mutie?

28
00:02:24.750 --> 00:02:28.333
So long as that collar stays on.
your powers are bye-bye.

29
00:02:28.417 --> 00:02:31.167
I'm not like the ones on TV.
I'm one of the good ones.

30
00:02:31.250 --> 00:02:32.375
A good mutant?

31
00:02:32.458 --> 00:02:33.750
Now. that is rich.

32
00:02:35.292 --> 00:02:37.083
Listen. I am begging you.

33
00:02:37.167 --> 00:02:38.667
I didn't ask for this. okay?

34
00:02:38.750 --> 00:02:39.792
I was born this way.

35
00:02:40.250 --> 00:02:41.750
Ain't that the rub?

36
00:02:42.208 --> 00:02:44.500
- [thunder rumbling]
- Hmm.

37
00:02:49.625 --> 00:02:52.833
-[thunder rumbling]
- [wind whooshing]

38
00:02:53.458 --> 00:02:55.625
[Denti] Grab a Sentinel blaster
and spread out!

39
00:02:55.708 --> 00:02:57.333
[blaster powering up]

40
00:02:57.417 --> 00:03:01.083
[Storm] I am Storm.
mistress of the elements.

41
00:03:01.708 --> 00:03:05.875
Surrender the boy or face my fury!

42
00:03:05.958 --> 00:03:07.167
[electricity crackling]

43
00:03:07.250 --> 00:03:09.208
I ain't afraid of you. you witch.

44
00:03:11.208 --> 00:03:12.667
Then you are a fool.

45
00:03:14.167 --> 00:03:15.417
[groans]

46
00:03:16.375 --> 00:03:17.375
Huh?

47
00:03:20.458 --> 00:03:23.417
Whole announcement shtick
didn't go over so well. did it?

48
00:03:23.500 --> 00:03:27.000
Pardon me. Bishop. for striving
to resolve matters peacefully.

49
00:03:28.000 --> 00:03:29.708
[Bishop] Real peaceful. Storm.

50
00:03:32.458 --> 00:03:33.917
Keep shooting. punks.

51
00:03:35.958 --> 00:03:39.458
Is it me. or did these dirtbags
get upgrades?

52
00:03:40.708 --> 00:03:41.708
Huh?

53
00:03:44.417 --> 00:03:46.917
[Denti] Boot it up. boys.
X-Men are like roaches.

54
00:03:47.000 --> 00:03:49.083
You see one. more are coming.

55
00:03:50.750 --> 00:03:52.083
[men scream]

56
00:03:57.042 --> 00:03:58.042
[speaks Portuguese]

57
00:03:58.125 --> 00:03:59.434
[in English] Good guy or bad guy?

58
00:03:59.458 --> 00:04:02.625
Name's Cyclops. Definitely the good guy.

59
00:04:06.042 --> 00:04:07.042
Hang tight.

60
00:04:10.458 --> 00:04:11.958
[grunting]

61
00:04:21.125 --> 00:04:22.125
[chuckles]

62
00:04:31.667 --> 00:04:33.292
- Kid. get down.
- [grunts]

63
00:04:41.083 --> 00:04:44.625
How'd scum like you get your hands
on Sentinel technology?

64
00:04:44.708 --> 00:04:47.958
What? You freak shows think
we wouldn't find a way to evolve. too?

65
00:04:48.042 --> 00:04:50.000
Take his visor before he starts up again.

66
00:04:50.083 --> 00:04:52.042
No. don't! I surrender!

67
00:04:53.583 --> 00:04:55.667
[chuckles] Not.

68
00:04:56.708 --> 00:04:58.250
[car alarm blaring]

69
00:05:02.500 --> 00:05:04.333
[Scott] Storm and Bishop
could have been hurt.

70
00:05:04.417 --> 00:05:05.875
We needed you out there.

71
00:05:05.958 --> 00:05:08.583
[Remy] You stopped the bad guys.
saved the kid.

72
00:05:08.667 --> 00:05:10.184
- got home safe.
- [♪ R&amp;B music playing]

73
00:05:10.208 --> 00:05:13.042
These beignets needed me
more than you did. <i>mon ami.</i>

74
00:05:13.125 --> 00:05:16.208
The Friends of Humanity
had retrofitted Sentinel weaponry.

75
00:05:16.292 --> 00:05:18.167
Do you have any idea
what that means. Gambit?

76
00:05:18.250 --> 00:05:22.500
Means you get to howling like
a lonely kettle left on a fiery stove.

77
00:05:22.583 --> 00:05:25.625
We've rodeo'd more Sentinels
than I care to count.

78
00:05:25.708 --> 00:05:28.625
And Storm and Bishop are made
of sterner stuff than you think.

79
00:05:28.708 --> 00:05:31.333
Rogue always come to Gambit's rescue.

80
00:05:31.417 --> 00:05:33.417
Rogue. the Professor entrusted us

81
00:05:33.500 --> 00:05:35.958
with his dream
of mutant-human coexistence.

82
00:05:36.042 --> 00:05:37.708
We have to stay vigilant.

83
00:05:37.792 --> 00:05:39.917
no matter how good things seem out there.

84
00:05:40.000 --> 00:05:41.583
The last few months have been rough.

85
00:05:41.667 --> 00:05:43.792
what with the Professor
being gone and all.

86
00:05:43.875 --> 00:05:47.333
but. sugar. if you don't simmer down.
you're gonna die of a stroke.

87
00:05:47.417 --> 00:05:48.958
[man] Rogue is right. Cyclops.

88
00:05:50.708 --> 00:05:54.542
Scott. while I trust that
all my students would gladly die

89
00:05:54.625 --> 00:05:56.708
for my dream of a better future.

90
00:05:56.792 --> 00:06:01.625
where both human and mutant
live free of your total disdain for fun.

91
00:06:01.708 --> 00:06:03.708
I would prefer it be avoided.

92
00:06:04.708 --> 00:06:06.375
Stop being a creep. Morph.

93
00:06:06.458 --> 00:06:07.958
[snickers]

94
00:06:10.458 --> 00:06:12.917
Look like Cyclops
about to have that stroke.

95
00:06:13.000 --> 00:06:14.583
Maybe this help.

96
00:06:19.208 --> 00:06:20.375
[explosion]

97
00:06:25.458 --> 00:06:28.458
- Remy. you could have hurt someone.
- [whistles]

98
00:06:28.542 --> 00:06:29.750
He doesn't care. Jean.

99
00:06:30.208 --> 00:06:32.750
All he cares about
are his stupid beignets.

100
00:06:32.833 --> 00:06:35.250
I don't know who's worse.
him or Wolverine.

101
00:06:35.333 --> 00:06:37.542
Well. can everyone just please behave?

102
00:06:37.625 --> 00:06:38.833
This is a school. after all.

103
00:06:38.917 --> 00:06:41.292
and we need to be role models
for our guest.

104
00:06:41.375 --> 00:06:42.375
[Scott] Jean's right.

105
00:06:42.458 --> 00:06:43.958
That kid's our only lead

106
00:06:44.042 --> 00:06:47.167
to where those extremists
got their hands on Sentinel tech.

107
00:06:48.042 --> 00:06:50.792
- [♪ opera music playing on stereo]
- [Beast humming]

108
00:06:50.875 --> 00:06:52.542
[groans] Huh?

109
00:06:52.625 --> 00:06:55.292
[Beast continues humming]

110
00:06:55.792 --> 00:06:56.792
Huh?

111
00:07:00.125 --> 00:07:01.125
Huh?

112
00:07:07.292 --> 00:07:08.708
Salutations and welcome.

113
00:07:09.417 --> 00:07:11.917
- I'm...
- Blue. very blue. Wow.

114
00:07:12.000 --> 00:07:13.958
An astute observation. my boy.

115
00:07:14.042 --> 00:07:15.125
Hank McCoy here.

116
00:07:15.208 --> 00:07:18.125
Or if you prefer my friendly
<i>nom de guerre.</i> Beast.

117
00:07:18.208 --> 00:07:20.792
- That there at the foot of your bed is...
- Name's Jubilee.

118
00:07:20.875 --> 00:07:22.375
And. dude. I get it.

119
00:07:22.458 --> 00:07:23.542
One day. life's fresh.

120
00:07:23.625 --> 00:07:25.125
Then the next day. you're waking up

121
00:07:25.208 --> 00:07:28.458
to a blue monkey singing Mozart
as he tinkers with doohickies.

122
00:07:28.542 --> 00:07:30.667
Simian analogies. Jubilee?

123
00:07:30.750 --> 00:07:32.042
Shame on you.

124
00:07:32.167 --> 00:07:34.625
And this doohickey
is an elegant piece of art

125
00:07:34.708 --> 00:07:37.083
capable of teleporting someone
through time and space.

126
00:07:37.625 --> 00:07:39.583
Bishop's bling. He's a time traveler.

127
00:07:41.875 --> 00:07:43.458
Hank. how fares the boy?

128
00:07:43.542 --> 00:07:47.583
Besides a cavity and layman's
existential fear of metaphysics.

129
00:07:47.667 --> 00:07:49.792
Mr. Da Costa here is in perfect health.

130
00:07:49.875 --> 00:07:51.792
I need to go. Where's my jacket?

131
00:07:51.875 --> 00:07:54.417
Tell me I didn't lose it. Super expensive.

132
00:07:54.500 --> 00:07:56.417
Roberto. we can't let you go just yet.

133
00:07:56.500 --> 00:07:59.875
- Oh. Right. How much?
- [Cyclops] "How much?"

134
00:07:59.958 --> 00:08:02.583
For the save? I was going to pay
those troops to free me. so...

135
00:08:02.667 --> 00:08:03.917
You take checks?

136
00:08:04.000 --> 00:08:07.375
We're more interested in the weapons
those creeps had.

137
00:08:07.458 --> 00:08:10.458
That giant arm was from a machine
called a Sentinel.

138
00:08:10.542 --> 00:08:13.708
Did your attackers say anything
about where they acquired it?

139
00:08:13.792 --> 00:08:15.417
Wait. wait. wait. wait. Hold up.

140
00:08:15.500 --> 00:08:18.333
Today's been a day and you're coming at me
with giant robot arms?

141
00:08:18.417 --> 00:08:21.792
Your attackers could still
be out there. child.

142
00:08:21.875 --> 00:08:23.458
Should we let you leave.

143
00:08:23.542 --> 00:08:26.167
they could find you and kill you.

144
00:08:26.250 --> 00:08:28.167
So now you're kidnapping me?

145
00:08:28.250 --> 00:08:29.333
Kidnapping?

146
00:08:29.417 --> 00:08:33.167
We wanna help mutants.
even arrogant yuppies like you.

147
00:08:34.542 --> 00:08:37.417
Look. you're scared. Roberto. I get it.

148
00:08:37.500 --> 00:08:39.333
Just give us the day to figure this out.

149
00:08:39.417 --> 00:08:40.625
make sure you're safe.

150
00:08:40.708 --> 00:08:44.375
and then you can go do
whatever a kid like you does.

151
00:08:44.458 --> 00:08:46.542
At least say there's something
to do around here

152
00:08:46.625 --> 00:08:47.917
besides listen to Mozart?

153
00:08:52.208 --> 00:08:56.792
Hear me. Humanity's days are over.

154
00:08:56.875 --> 00:09:00.125
We are nature's favored children.

155
00:09:00.208 --> 00:09:02.250
Our new age begins

156
00:09:02.333 --> 00:09:06.292
as we build a bright mutant future.

157
00:09:06.750 --> 00:09:08.333
Video games are for nerds.

158
00:09:08.417 --> 00:09:10.208
[Jubilee] <i>Oh. it's no game. buddy.</i>

159
00:09:10.292 --> 00:09:12.542
<i>It's the Danger Room. It's where we train.</i>

160
00:09:12.625 --> 00:09:15.542
That's Magneto. the Professor's ex-bestie.

161
00:09:15.625 --> 00:09:19.417
They had. uh. different takes
on mutant-human coexistence.

162
00:09:19.500 --> 00:09:20.708
So what can you do?

163
00:09:20.792 --> 00:09:21.833
Fly. teleport?

164
00:09:21.917 --> 00:09:24.250
<i>Shoot gold balls from your body?
That'd be weird.</i>

165
00:09:24.333 --> 00:09:25.917
But. like. he's not even real.

166
00:09:26.000 --> 00:09:28.417
You would turn your back on your own?

167
00:09:32.542 --> 00:09:34.625
[pants. grunts]

168
00:09:36.208 --> 00:09:38.875
[Jubilee] <i>Better show me those powers.</i>
<i>tough guy.</i>

169
00:09:38.958 --> 00:09:40.625
Seriously. girl. get a life.

170
00:09:40.708 --> 00:09:42.083
[grunts]

171
00:09:42.167 --> 00:09:43.167
[gasps]

172
00:09:43.250 --> 00:09:44.917
Show the lady some respect.

173
00:09:45.000 --> 00:09:48.542
Oh. so scary. Jubilee. Can we stop now?

174
00:09:48.625 --> 00:09:51.625
- Computer. end program.
- [gasps]

175
00:09:53.083 --> 00:09:55.833
- [gasps]
- Scary enough for you. bub?

176
00:09:56.583 --> 00:10:00.292
[Dr. Cooper] <i>Agencies in the US. England</i>
<i>and Madripoor have been catching rumors</i>

177
00:10:00.375 --> 00:10:02.333
<i>of anti-mutant militias
with Sentinel weaponry.</i>

178
00:10:02.417 --> 00:10:05.292
<i>But this is the first I've heard
of any confirmed reports.</i>

179
00:10:05.375 --> 00:10:07.215
[Scott] How are these groups
getting this tech?

180
00:10:07.292 --> 00:10:09.500
You said the UN destroyed
all the Sentinels.

181
00:10:09.583 --> 00:10:10.583
<i>And we did.</i>

182
00:10:10.667 --> 00:10:14.458
Oh. I guess I just imagined the big
robot hand that almost took out my team.

183
00:10:14.542 --> 00:10:16.208
Someone's putting this stuff out there.

184
00:10:16.292 --> 00:10:18.708
Dr. Cooper. what about Bolivar Trask?

185
00:10:18.792 --> 00:10:20.958
<i>Trask's been missing
ever since his inventions tried</i>

186
00:10:21.042 --> 00:10:24.292
<i>to swap out President Kelly's brain
with a Sentinel computer.</i>

187
00:10:24.583 --> 00:10:27.000
<i>He'd need a Master Mold factory
to build new Sentinels</i>

188
00:10:27.083 --> 00:10:29.875
<i>and you X-Men destroyed
the only one years ago.</i>

189
00:10:29.958 --> 00:10:31.458
Well. when cardio wraps.

190
00:10:31.542 --> 00:10:33.042
maybe you can spare the calories

191
00:10:33.125 --> 00:10:35.000
to go make sure
he didn't build another one.

192
00:10:35.708 --> 00:10:37.917
<i>Charles Xavier was a dear friend of mine.</i>

193
00:10:38.000 --> 00:10:41.375
<i>It's why I urged the UN Council
to work with the X-Men.</i>

194
00:10:41.458 --> 00:10:43.333
<i>A little trust. Scott.</i>

195
00:10:43.417 --> 00:10:47.458
The Professor loved to say.
"Trust happens when actions meet words."

196
00:10:47.542 --> 00:10:48.583
Cyclops out.

197
00:10:53.667 --> 00:10:55.750
[laughter. chattering]

198
00:10:58.917 --> 00:11:00.833
[Jean] Well.
this certainly explains your mood.

199
00:11:01.667 --> 00:11:03.625
Yeah. it came yesterday.

200
00:11:04.417 --> 00:11:07.417
You know. if he were here.
the team wouldn't be shooting hoops

201
00:11:07.500 --> 00:11:09.458
while slime like the Friends of Humanity

202
00:11:09.542 --> 00:11:11.542
are running around with Sentinel blasters.

203
00:11:11.625 --> 00:11:14.458
[Jean] You're too hard on yourself.
and the team.

204
00:11:14.542 --> 00:11:17.417
Remember when we were young
and we'd sneak down to the lake

205
00:11:17.500 --> 00:11:19.625
instead of doing our Danger Room drills?

206
00:11:20.250 --> 00:11:23.750
[chuckles] Oh. yeah.
The Professor would shout.

207
00:11:23.833 --> 00:11:27.750
"Your childish hijinks
have cost you five demerits. young man."

208
00:11:27.833 --> 00:11:29.873
[chuckles] And you'd say.
[in deep voice] "But. sir.

209
00:11:29.917 --> 00:11:33.375
"what's the point of being an X-Man
if we're not allowed to enjoy our lives?"

210
00:11:33.750 --> 00:11:35.583
Whoa. whoa. I did not sound like that.

211
00:11:35.667 --> 00:11:37.167
Oh. yes. you did.

212
00:11:37.250 --> 00:11:39.417
- You still sound like that.
- [chuckles]

213
00:11:40.042 --> 00:11:43.208
Those days have been on my mind
a lot lately. darling.

214
00:11:43.292 --> 00:11:46.917
You and I alone.
Our whole future ahead of us.

215
00:11:47.792 --> 00:11:50.167
The team. they'll always be family.

216
00:11:50.250 --> 00:11:52.750
but with the baby coming.

217
00:11:53.250 --> 00:11:56.792
maybe it's time to think of a life
beyond the X-Men?

218
00:11:56.875 --> 00:12:00.542
"Beyond"? You mean leave the team? Jean.

219
00:12:00.625 --> 00:12:02.000
It's like you said. Scott.

220
00:12:02.083 --> 00:12:04.042
What have we been fighting for
all these years

221
00:12:04.125 --> 00:12:06.667
if not the chance
to finally live our lives?

222
00:12:06.750 --> 00:12:09.083
We were the Professor's first students.

223
00:12:09.167 --> 00:12:10.875
The X-Men need us here.

224
00:12:10.958 --> 00:12:12.708
The team will be fine.

225
00:12:13.917 --> 00:12:15.917
Our son will need us more.

226
00:12:16.458 --> 00:12:19.417
Deep down. you know that.

227
00:12:19.917 --> 00:12:23.333
And I know it hurts.
But this one time. Scott...

228
00:12:24.708 --> 00:12:26.833
It's okay for you to let go.

229
00:12:27.292 --> 00:12:28.667
- [Jubilee] Jerk!
- [glass breaks]

230
00:12:30.833 --> 00:12:32.083
[glass shatters]

231
00:12:38.250 --> 00:12:41.167
- [chuckles]
- [Jean] Jubilee! What are you doing?

232
00:12:41.250 --> 00:12:43.208
Bozo here scared Roberto off.

233
00:12:43.292 --> 00:12:47.042
Cyclops. what if those creeps
with the Sentinel gizmos find him?

234
00:12:47.125 --> 00:12:51.958
[sighs] Logan. take that nose of yours
and go find the kid.

235
00:12:52.042 --> 00:12:53.458
- And take Jubilee.
- [growls]

236
00:12:53.542 --> 00:12:56.542
Actually. all of you could stand
to act a little more like X-Men.

237
00:12:56.625 --> 00:12:57.625
Go with them.

238
00:12:57.708 --> 00:13:00.042
Hey. now. we didn't do a dang thing.

239
00:13:00.125 --> 00:13:02.000
Took the words right out of my mouth.

240
00:13:02.083 --> 00:13:05.083
Jean may dig
the Boy Scout routine. Summers.

241
00:13:05.167 --> 00:13:08.708
but I don't much go in
for being bossed around.

242
00:13:08.792 --> 00:13:11.292
Cry me a river. Wolverine.

243
00:13:12.625 --> 00:13:13.750
[Jean] Logan...

244
00:13:15.250 --> 00:13:16.667
Find Roberto.

245
00:13:17.542 --> 00:13:18.583
please.

246
00:13:21.667 --> 00:13:23.792
What Gyrich did was pretty horrible.

247
00:13:23.875 --> 00:13:27.042
But want to know the worst part
about the Professor being gone?

248
00:13:27.708 --> 00:13:28.875
You.

249
00:13:32.917 --> 00:13:35.500
- He didn't mean it.
- Doesn't matter.

250
00:13:36.042 --> 00:13:38.875
I know who we need to see
to find Bolivar Trask.

251
00:13:39.375 --> 00:13:41.917
The man who killed Charles Xavier.

252
00:13:43.375 --> 00:13:46.208
[♪ dance music playing]

253
00:13:52.167 --> 00:13:55.167
The kid's here.
but there are too many damn scents.

254
00:13:55.250 --> 00:13:56.667
Looks like we split up.

255
00:13:56.750 --> 00:13:59.542
Nice place to pass a good time. eh. <i>chère?</i>

256
00:14:17.000 --> 00:14:21.167
[sighs] If I was down there
and one of 'em brushed against my skin.

257
00:14:21.250 --> 00:14:25.208
my power-sappin' touch would leave 'em
with a nasty hangover.

258
00:14:25.292 --> 00:14:29.583
Any worthwhile man would
gladly suffer your hand in a dance.

259
00:14:36.375 --> 00:14:38.917
Thought you were gonna
slice Summers' head off back there.

260
00:14:39.458 --> 00:14:40.583
Wanna talk about it?

261
00:14:40.667 --> 00:14:44.250
Let's just find this trust-fund baby
and get out of here. Morph.

262
00:14:46.042 --> 00:14:48.250
I know what's wrong. How?

263
00:14:48.333 --> 00:14:52.167
Why. I'm Jean Grey.
humble telepath extraordinaire.

264
00:14:52.250 --> 00:14:55.000
and I'm having the most
beautiful baby in the world

265
00:14:55.083 --> 00:14:57.375
with the most boring man in the world.

266
00:14:57.458 --> 00:15:00.292
and. "Oh. hello. you on the sidelines.

267
00:15:00.375 --> 00:15:03.458
"watching our exhausting perfection
every day."

268
00:15:03.542 --> 00:15:08.292
Perfection? If we ain't fighting Magneto.
we're dodging aliens and Sentinels.

269
00:15:08.375 --> 00:15:10.375
School's no place for a baby.

270
00:15:10.458 --> 00:15:12.750
You... Jean knows as much.

271
00:15:12.833 --> 00:15:15.500
- You don't think...
- They're leaving the team. Morph.

272
00:15:15.583 --> 00:15:16.792
Jean's leaving.

273
00:15:19.042 --> 00:15:21.458
[♪ music continues playing]

274
00:15:25.250 --> 00:15:26.792
[people cheering]

275
00:15:32.000 --> 00:15:34.292
No. no. I'm not going back there.

276
00:15:34.375 --> 00:15:36.917
Dork. let's go. You're not safe here.

277
00:15:37.000 --> 00:15:39.708
One dance. then I'll come. Promise.

278
00:15:47.583 --> 00:15:49.250
[firecrackers bursting]

279
00:15:56.917 --> 00:15:58.417
Beats that stuffy mansion. right?

280
00:15:58.500 --> 00:16:01.250
Hey. at least they're not
wasting time partying

281
00:16:01.333 --> 00:16:02.833
when they could be helping people.

282
00:16:02.917 --> 00:16:06.542
And waste the best years of my life
on some bald guy's corny dream?

283
00:16:06.625 --> 00:16:09.708
Of course. someone like you
would find a little selflessness corny.

284
00:16:09.792 --> 00:16:11.375
Peace. love. I get it.

285
00:16:11.458 --> 00:16:13.792
Does he have to make
such a big stink about it?

286
00:16:13.875 --> 00:16:17.125
Is that why you didn't use your powers
against those goons?

287
00:16:17.208 --> 00:16:19.167
Didn't want to rub their faces in it?

288
00:16:19.250 --> 00:16:20.917
It's like <i>minha mãe</i> says. Jubilee.

289
00:16:21.000 --> 00:16:22.167
[speaks Portuguese]

290
00:16:22.250 --> 00:16:23.490
[in English] Live and let live.

291
00:16:23.542 --> 00:16:25.292
Sometimes people don't get along.

292
00:16:25.375 --> 00:16:26.750
[Logan] Don't I know it. bub?

293
00:16:26.833 --> 00:16:29.250
FOH ran when they saw us coming.

294
00:16:29.333 --> 00:16:31.500
Dropped one of their little toys. too.

295
00:16:31.583 --> 00:16:35.042
Pray Cyclops find where these bad boys
are coming from.

296
00:16:35.125 --> 00:16:36.750
before things get too hot to handle.

297
00:16:40.000 --> 00:16:43.750
I can't believe this fool
nearly cost us the whole future.

298
00:16:43.833 --> 00:16:45.667
He still cost us enough.

299
00:16:47.542 --> 00:16:49.875
Why would I know where Trask is?

300
00:16:49.958 --> 00:16:52.833
You helped fund his Sentinel program

301
00:16:52.917 --> 00:16:55.125
when you worked
for the Defense Department.

302
00:16:55.208 --> 00:16:57.958
[Scott] Gyrich. you're serving 25 years.

303
00:16:58.042 --> 00:17:00.333
- You talk and I get it down to 10.
- [whistles]

304
00:17:00.417 --> 00:17:04.542
You mutants are moving up.
making friends in high places.

305
00:17:05.042 --> 00:17:08.042
Though it's got to hurt.
offering that deal to me.

306
00:17:08.125 --> 00:17:10.708
Those Sentinel upgrades really threw you.

307
00:17:10.792 --> 00:17:15.000
We merely hoped some humans
had evolved beyond the past.

308
00:17:15.083 --> 00:17:17.833
[scoffs] Did you honestly think
we'd roll over

309
00:17:17.917 --> 00:17:20.292
and let mutants take over the planet?

310
00:17:20.375 --> 00:17:21.875
That we wouldn't fight back?

311
00:17:21.958 --> 00:17:27.250
Yet your cruelty has only made
humanity more sympathetic to our cause.

312
00:17:27.667 --> 00:17:29.042
Oh. did it?

313
00:17:29.125 --> 00:17:32.500
No. you're in vogue. Storm. A fad.

314
00:17:32.583 --> 00:17:34.500
"Look at my mutant friend."

315
00:17:35.042 --> 00:17:37.792
But under all that fashionable sympathy.

316
00:17:37.875 --> 00:17:42.000
normal people know
the more room we make for your kind.

317
00:17:42.083 --> 00:17:44.167
the less we leave for ours.

318
00:17:44.250 --> 00:17:47.042
So we might wear tolerance on our sleeves.

319
00:17:47.125 --> 00:17:49.125
but we know the naked truth.

320
00:17:49.208 --> 00:17:52.125
Tolerance is extinction.

321
00:17:53.375 --> 00:17:55.958
Ten years. Gyrich. Yours to win or lose.

322
00:17:56.625 --> 00:18:00.750
I won the day I shot the man
you freak shows look up to.

323
00:18:00.833 --> 00:18:03.583
And you get an "A" for effort.
Mr. Summers.

324
00:18:03.667 --> 00:18:06.667
but we both know you're no Charles Xavier.

325
00:18:06.750 --> 00:18:09.500
You're right. I'm not Charles Xavier.

326
00:18:09.583 --> 00:18:11.792
He'd reason with you. Be patient.

327
00:18:11.875 --> 00:18:14.833
He'd do everything in his power
to save you.

328
00:18:14.917 --> 00:18:17.917
Save me? From what. you?

329
00:18:19.083 --> 00:18:21.458
No. But have you met my wife?

330
00:18:22.583 --> 00:18:25.542
Hatred weakens your mind. Mr. Gyrich.

331
00:18:25.625 --> 00:18:28.917
- [groans]
- Cerebro amplifies my psychic powers.

332
00:18:29.000 --> 00:18:33.042
allowing me to penetrate
your thoughts from any distance I please.

333
00:18:33.125 --> 00:18:34.792
[Gyrich] Get out of my head!

334
00:18:34.875 --> 00:18:37.750
[Bolivar] <i>One Master Mold is not enough.</i>
<i>We need backups.</i>

335
00:18:37.833 --> 00:18:39.125
<i>I know a place.</i>

336
00:18:41.333 --> 00:18:43.625
Something's wrong. Someone else...

337
00:18:44.500 --> 00:18:45.833
[screams]

338
00:18:53.167 --> 00:18:54.250
Whoa!

339
00:18:58.292 --> 00:19:01.042
- [gasps]
- [baby crying]

340
00:19:05.917 --> 00:19:07.208
[baby coos]

341
00:19:11.042 --> 00:19:15.042
[male voice] <i>No! Not again. I'm so sorry.</i>

342
00:19:21.333 --> 00:19:23.333
[rumbling]

343
00:19:27.250 --> 00:19:32.542
[Master Mold] <i>Behold. mutant. and despair.</i>
<i>for I am Death.</i>

344
00:19:32.625 --> 00:19:35.667
<i>I am Master Mold.</i>

345
00:19:40.750 --> 00:19:42.042
[screams]

346
00:19:42.125 --> 00:19:44.083
[Scott over speakers] <i>Jean! Jean. come in!</i>

347
00:19:44.167 --> 00:19:46.125
I'm here. I'm here. Scott.

348
00:19:46.208 --> 00:19:48.042
[pants] I'm fine.

349
00:19:48.125 --> 00:19:49.667
What I felt...

350
00:19:49.750 --> 00:19:52.250
We have to stop Trask. Now.

351
00:19:53.250 --> 00:19:54.309
[Cyclops] Listen up. people.

352
00:19:54.333 --> 00:19:57.375
Jean's psychic scan placed Trask
in the Sahara Desert.

353
00:19:57.458 --> 00:19:59.708
We fly into the coordinates. detain Trask

354
00:19:59.792 --> 00:20:01.875
and shut down Master Mold for good.

355
00:20:01.958 --> 00:20:03.833
I say we skip detaining

356
00:20:03.917 --> 00:20:07.458
and mail Trask back to the UN
in little pieces.

357
00:20:07.542 --> 00:20:11.000
[chuckles] There will be
no dismembering. Wolverine.

358
00:20:11.083 --> 00:20:12.167
[Wolverine] Dismembering?

359
00:20:12.250 --> 00:20:14.958
Nah. Weight loss.

360
00:20:15.042 --> 00:20:17.208
We get this done
by working together as a team.

361
00:20:17.917 --> 00:20:19.583
Think you can do that. Logan?

362
00:20:19.667 --> 00:20:22.250
Jeez. Dad. Keep buzzing in my ear.

363
00:20:22.333 --> 00:20:24.583
What would we do if we ever lost you?

364
00:20:24.792 --> 00:20:26.708
- [rumbling]
- [all exclaiming]

365
00:20:26.792 --> 00:20:27.917
[alarms blaring]

366
00:20:28.000 --> 00:20:29.375
Hang on. people.

367
00:20:33.792 --> 00:20:35.250
[Storm] Cyclops!

368
00:20:42.250 --> 00:20:43.917
[all scream]

369
00:21:03.500 --> 00:21:05.500
[Rogue] Another "catch the X-Men" day.

370
00:21:07.667 --> 00:21:10.542
Solid work. team. See you on the ground.

371
00:21:18.333 --> 00:21:19.333
[Cyclops yells]

372
00:21:34.958 --> 00:21:37.083
To me. my X-Men.

373
00:21:44.125 --> 00:21:45.292
[chuckles]

374
00:21:49.958 --> 00:21:51.917
[Bolivar] Gyrich warned me
you were coming.

375
00:21:52.000 --> 00:21:53.708
Even in prison. he has friends

376
00:21:53.792 --> 00:21:56.917
who know the mutant agenda
must be stopped.

377
00:21:57.000 --> 00:21:58.708
[Cyclops] Trask. we don't want to fight.

378
00:22:02.167 --> 00:22:04.667
[Bolivar] You mutants may be
the next step in evolution.

379
00:22:04.750 --> 00:22:06.792
but you're still animals

380
00:22:06.875 --> 00:22:09.333
and you need to be put down.

381
00:22:09.667 --> 00:22:11.375
Final warning. Trask.

382
00:22:13.958 --> 00:22:15.333
[rumbling]

383
00:22:17.833 --> 00:22:19.208
[Sentinel]<i> Surrender. mutant.</i>

384
00:22:21.292 --> 00:22:25.875
[Sentinels] <i>Surrender. mutant.</i>
<i>Surrender. mutant. Surrender. mutant.</i>

385
00:22:38.542 --> 00:22:39.542
Head's up.

386
00:22:52.417 --> 00:22:54.000
Greetings. enemy mine.

387
00:22:54.542 --> 00:22:57.000
Might I induce you to a change of heart?

388
00:22:58.208 --> 00:23:01.542
Louis. I think this is the beginning
of a beautiful. involuntary friendship.

389
00:23:23.917 --> 00:23:25.125
[Sentinels] <i>Surrender. mutant.</i>

390
00:23:25.208 --> 00:23:26.583
<i>Surrender. mutant.</i>

391
00:23:27.750 --> 00:23:29.375
Give 'em the forecast.

392
00:23:30.625 --> 00:23:33.208
<i>Omega-level threat detected.</i>

393
00:23:40.625 --> 00:23:42.375
[thunder rumbling]

394
00:23:46.250 --> 00:23:49.958
Ancient sands. heed my command

395
00:23:50.042 --> 00:23:53.042
and reclaim these relics of hatred.

396
00:24:12.750 --> 00:24:13.750
Huh?

397
00:24:17.833 --> 00:24:21.417
[Master Mold]
<i>You underestimate us. mutant.</i>

398
00:24:31.583 --> 00:24:33.333
Morph. belly up.

399
00:24:55.375 --> 00:24:58.875
You X-Men might use your gifts
to protect everyone.

400
00:24:58.958 --> 00:25:02.042
but all you do is remind us
that our days are numbered.

401
00:25:02.125 --> 00:25:05.083
that humanity itself is obsolete.

402
00:25:05.167 --> 00:25:08.958
You've no idea how it feels
to be left behind by the future.

403
00:25:10.792 --> 00:25:14.250
Our Special Sciences Division
is flying in to dismantle Master Mold.

404
00:25:14.750 --> 00:25:17.708
Yet again.
humanity is in the X-Men's debt.

405
00:25:18.667 --> 00:25:22.167
Trask would rather humans and mutants
go to war than work together.

406
00:25:22.250 --> 00:25:24.708
We all win when men like him fail.

407
00:25:24.792 --> 00:25:26.625
You sound like Charles.

408
00:25:26.708 --> 00:25:28.208
He would have been proud today.

409
00:25:30.667 --> 00:25:34.708
Thank you. Dr. Cooper.
But to be honest. it was a team effort.

410
00:25:36.458 --> 00:25:37.833
Always has been.

411
00:25:40.292 --> 00:25:41.684
[Jubilee] Team's on their way back.

412
00:25:41.708 --> 00:25:42.792
Mission accomplished.

413
00:25:42.875 --> 00:25:46.208
Freedom! I mean.
I'll get out of your hair.

414
00:25:47.000 --> 00:25:50.042
Look. I know today was strange.

415
00:25:50.125 --> 00:25:53.625
When I first came here.
I ran away. just like you.

416
00:25:54.167 --> 00:25:56.958
The team had saved me
from Sentinels at the mall.

417
00:25:57.042 --> 00:25:58.042
But this place.

418
00:25:58.125 --> 00:26:02.958
a place where I could be me.
where a foster brat belonged.

419
00:26:03.042 --> 00:26:06.125
that was scarier than any killer robot.

420
00:26:06.208 --> 00:26:09.375
Sure. Cyclops still won't
let me fly the jet.

421
00:26:09.458 --> 00:26:11.500
but this isn't some weird school.

422
00:26:12.375 --> 00:26:13.458
It's a family.

423
00:26:14.500 --> 00:26:15.875
A family that accepts you.

424
00:26:16.958 --> 00:26:18.042
Sounds nice.

425
00:26:19.458 --> 00:26:21.833
Your parents don't know. do they?

426
00:26:22.458 --> 00:26:23.458
[sighs]

427
00:26:24.958 --> 00:26:27.083
[Roberto] Some sort of solar energy.

428
00:26:27.167 --> 00:26:28.500
Still figuring it out.

429
00:26:28.583 --> 00:26:31.083
Makes me strong. though. Really strong.

430
00:26:31.167 --> 00:26:34.292
Whenever I do this.
it just reminds me that I'm different.

431
00:26:34.375 --> 00:26:36.000
That I'm lying to them.

432
00:26:36.833 --> 00:26:38.292
Be an X-Man. Jubilee?

433
00:26:39.208 --> 00:26:40.625
I don't even want to be myself.

434
00:26:44.250 --> 00:26:45.375
[speaks Portuguese]

435
00:26:45.458 --> 00:26:46.958
- [in English] Here.
- Mmm.

436
00:26:47.042 --> 00:26:48.792
What's your job? Hot and rich?

437
00:26:48.875 --> 00:26:50.417
Don't forget single.

438
00:26:50.500 --> 00:26:52.792
Page me. I got a jet. too.

439
00:26:52.875 --> 00:26:54.792
Maybe I'll even let you fly it.

440
00:26:57.750 --> 00:27:00.083
- [indistinct chatter]
- [blowing whistle]

441
00:27:00.167 --> 00:27:01.958
Remember. no powers.

442
00:27:02.042 --> 00:27:04.333
What about Gambit's other powers?

443
00:27:04.417 --> 00:27:06.042
[grunts] Ow!

444
00:27:06.125 --> 00:27:10.042
The responsibility to choose teams
falls to team leader.

445
00:27:11.958 --> 00:27:14.833
I know I've been hardheaded lately.
It's just... [sighs]

446
00:27:14.917 --> 00:27:17.542
I didn't know how the X-Men
could go on without the Professor.

447
00:27:18.208 --> 00:27:19.542
Thought it was on me.

448
00:27:20.208 --> 00:27:23.000
But his dream doesn't need me.

449
00:27:23.625 --> 00:27:24.750
It has all of you.

450
00:27:25.417 --> 00:27:29.250
And with that said.
Jean and I have an announcement.

451
00:27:29.333 --> 00:27:33.417
You're bailing on us to go raise
your little one someplace nice and normal.

452
00:27:33.500 --> 00:27:35.500
Logan. we're not bailing.

453
00:27:35.833 --> 00:27:38.917
Uh. Cyclops and Jean were the first X-Men.

454
00:27:39.000 --> 00:27:42.000
If they're gone.
who the heck is going to lead the team?

455
00:27:42.083 --> 00:27:43.934
- [alarm rings]
- [automated voice] <i>Intruder alert!</i>

456
00:27:43.958 --> 00:27:47.292
Sensors show the intruder
has breached the Professor's old office.

457
00:27:49.833 --> 00:27:53.583
[man] Charles Xavier
was the finest man I knew.

458
00:27:53.667 --> 00:27:55.625
Despite our differences.

459
00:27:55.708 --> 00:27:58.042
he never ceased
to have faith in our friendship.

460
00:27:58.125 --> 00:28:00.458
nor forgive my many failings.

461
00:28:00.542 --> 00:28:04.208
Perhaps that is why
the old fool has done this.

462
00:28:04.292 --> 00:28:07.250
[Scott] Magneto.
what are you doing in our home?

463
00:28:07.333 --> 00:28:10.958
Your home? I beg to differ. Cyclops.

464
00:28:11.042 --> 00:28:15.917
The last will and testament
of Charles Francis Xavier.

465
00:28:16.000 --> 00:28:17.958
As you all will see.

466
00:28:18.042 --> 00:28:20.875
his fortune. his school.

467
00:28:20.958 --> 00:28:25.250
everything he built.
everything he fought for.

468
00:28:25.792 --> 00:28:30.125
now belongs to me. my X-Men.
